        <h2>📌 How to Read the Weather Report?</h2>

        <p><strong>Condition:</strong> This describes the current weather (e.g., Clear, Cloudy, Rainy).</p>
        <p><strong>Temperature:</strong> The report gives the current temperature in Fahrenheit or Celsius (e.g., It is currently 73°F out).</p>
        <p><strong>Chance of Rain:</strong> This shows the likelihood of rain (e.g., There is a 0% chance of rain means no rain expected).</p>

        <h2>🌍 Example Weather Report & What It Means</h2>
        <p>👉 <strong>"Clear. It is currently 73°F out. There is a 0% chance of rain."</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>✔ The sky is clear, with no clouds or rain.</li>
            <li>✔ The temperature is warm and comfortable.</li>
            <li>✔ No rain expected, so it’s a great time for outdoor activities!</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>❓ Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p><strong>🔹 What does “partly cloudy” mean?</strong><br>
        It means the sky has some clouds, but there’s still plenty of sunlight.</p>

        <p><strong>🔹 What if the chance of rain is 50%?</strong><br>
        This means there’s an equal chance of rain and dry weather—carry an umbrella just in case!</p>

        <p><strong>🔹 How often is the weather updated?</strong><br>
        Our data refreshes regularly to provide the latest weather conditions.</p>
